			"previous": " Maria Ursula her parents and both children died in September 1833 from cholera 59  On April 25 1831 Bowie married nineteen year old Maria Ursula de Veramendi the daughter of his business partner who had become the vice governor of the province Several days before the ceremony he signed a dowry contract promising to pay his new bride 15 000 pesos approximately 15 000 then or 332 000 today 55 in cash or property within two years of the marriage At the time Bowie claimed to have a net worth of 223 000 4 940 000 today mostly in land of questionable title Bowie also lied about his age claiming to be 30 rather than 35 56 The couple built a house in San Antonio on land Veramendi had given them near the San Jos Mission After a short time however they moved into the Veramendi Palace living with Ursula s parents who supplied them with spending money 57 The couple had two children Marie Elve b March 20 1832 and James Veramendi b July 18 1833 58 ",
